Engineers at the DFKI Robotics Centre in Bremen describe the EOssc2 as an 'ultra flexible micro-car for mega cities' The concept car can turn on the spot, shrink in size and even move sideways . 
  It is designed to connect to others to form a train and is currently being tested in the cities of B Remen and Dalian . 
  The car is intended to be semi-autonomous and can drive itself . 
